\frac{y-5}{x+1}=\frac{5-0}{-1-t}=\frac{-5}{1+t}
\implies \frac {x+1}{t+1}=\frac{y-5}{-5}=\sqrt{\frac{(x+1)^2+(y-5)^2}{(t+1)^2+(-5)^2}}
\implies \frac {x+1}{\frac{t+1}{\sqrt{(t+1)^2+25}}}=\frac{y-5}{\frac{-5}{\sqrt{(t+1)^2+25}}}=\sqrt{(x+1)^2+(y-5)^2}
\frac{t+1}{\sqrt{(t+1)^2+(-5)^2}}=\cos\theta=\frac45
\implies  t+1>0\text{ and }\{5(t+1)\}^2=4\{(t+1)^2+(-5)^2\}
